Index functions

Menu functions
	<bottom-page>     OP_BOTTOM_PAGE     move to the bottom of the page
	<current-bottom>  OP_CURRENT_BOTTOM  move entry to bottom of screen
	<current-middle>  OP_CURRENT_MIDDLE  move entry to middle of screen
	<current-top>     OP_CURRENT_TOP     move entry to top of screen
	<first-entry>     OP_FIRST_ENTRY     move to the first entry
	<half-down>       OP_HALF_DOWN       scroll down 1/2 page
	<half-up>         OP_HALF_UP         scroll up 1/2 page
	<jump>            OP_JUMP            jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_1          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_2          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_3          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_4          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_5          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_6          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_7          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_8          jump to an index number
	<jump>            OP_JUMP_9          jump to an index number
	<last-entry>      OP_LAST_ENTRY      move to the last entry
	<middle-page>     OP_MIDDLE_PAGE     move to the middle of the page
	<next-entry>      OP_NEXT_ENTRY      move to the next entry
	<next-line>       OP_NEXT_LINE       scroll down one line
	<next-page>       OP_NEXT_PAGE       move to the next page
	<previous-entry>  OP_PREV_ENTRY      move to the previous entry
	<previous-line>   OP_PREV_LINE       scroll up one line
	<previous-page>   OP_PREV_PAGE       move to the previous page
	<search>          OP_SEARCH          search for a regular expression
	<search-next>     OP_SEARCH_NEXT     search for next match
	<search-opposite> OP_SEARCH_OPPOSITE search for next match in opposite direction
	<search-reverse>  OP_SEARCH_REVERSE  search backwards for a regular expression
	<top-page>        OP_TOP_PAGE        move to the top of the page

Thread functions
	<break-thread>                OP_MAIN_BREAK_THREAD                break the thread in two
	<delete-subthread>            OP_DELETE_SUBTHREAD                 delete all messages in subthread
	<delete-thread>               OP_DELETE_THREAD                    delete all messages in thread
	<entire-thread>               OP_MAIN_ENTIRE_THREAD               read entire thread of the current message
	<link-threads>                OP_MAIN_LINK_THREADS                link tagged message to the current one
	<purge-thread>                OP_PURGE_THREAD                     delete the current thread, bypassing the trash folder
	<read-subthread>              OP_MAIN_READ_SUBTHREAD              mark the current subthread as read
	<read-thread>                 OP_MAIN_READ_THREAD                 mark the current thread as read
	<reconstruct-thread>          OP_RECONSTRUCT_THREAD               reconstruct thread containing current message
	<undelete-subthread>          OP_UNDELETE_SUBTHREAD               undelete all messages in subthread
	<undelete-thread>             OP_UNDELETE_THREAD                  undelete all messages in thread

MailboxView functions
	<collapse-all>                OP_MAIN_COLLAPSE_ALL                collapse/uncollapse all threads
	<collapse-thread>             OP_MAIN_COLLAPSE_THREAD             collapse/uncollapse current thread
	<limit-current-thread>        OP_LIMIT_CURRENT_THREAD             limit view to current thread
	<limit>                       OP_MAIN_LIMIT                       show only messages matching a pattern
	<next-subthread>              OP_MAIN_NEXT_SUBTHREAD              jump to the next subthread
	<next-thread>                 OP_MAIN_NEXT_THREAD                 jump to the next thread
	<parent-message>              OP_MAIN_PARENT_MESSAGE              jump to parent message in thread
	<previous-subthread>          OP_MAIN_PREV_SUBTHREAD              jump to previous subthread
	<previous-thread>             OP_MAIN_PREV_THREAD                 jump to previous thread
	<root-message>                OP_MAIN_ROOT_MESSAGE                jump to root message in thread
	<sort-reverse>                OP_SORT_REVERSE                     sort messages in reverse order
	<sort>                        OP_SORT                             sort messages
	<tag-message>                 OP_TAG                              tag the current entry
	<tag-pattern>                 OP_MAIN_TAG_PATTERN                 tag non-hidden messages matching a pattern
	<tag-subthread>               OP_TAG_SUBTHREAD                    tag the current subthread
	<tag-thread>                  OP_TAG_THREAD                       tag the current thread
	<toggle-read>                 OP_TOGGLE_READ                      toggle view of read messages
	<untag-pattern>               OP_MAIN_UNTAG_PATTERN               untag non-hidden messages matching a pattern

Global functions
	<check-stats>       OP_CHECK_STATS       calculate message statistics for all mailboxes
	<enter-command>     OP_ENTER_COMMAND     enter a neomuttrc command
	<refresh>           OP_REDRAW            clear and redraw the screen
	<shell-escape>      OP_SHELL_ESCAPE      invoke a command in a subshell
	<show-log-messages> OP_SHOW_LOG_MESSAGES show log (and debug) messages
	<show-version>      OP_VERSION           show the NeoMutt version number and date
	<what-key>          OP_WHAT_KEY          display the keycode for a key press

Sidebar functions
	<sidebar-first>          OP_SIDEBAR_FIRST          move the highlight to the first mailbox
	<sidebar-last>           OP_SIDEBAR_LAST           move the highlight to the last mailbox
	<sidebar-next-new>       OP_SIDEBAR_NEXT_NEW       move the highlight to next mailbox with new mail
	<sidebar-next>           OP_SIDEBAR_NEXT           move the highlight to next mailbox
	<sidebar-open>           OP_SIDEBAR_OPEN           open highlighted mailbox
	<sidebar-page-down>      OP_SIDEBAR_PAGE_DOWN      scroll the sidebar down 1 page
	<sidebar-page-up>        OP_SIDEBAR_PAGE_UP        scroll the sidebar up 1 page
	<sidebar-prev-new>       OP_SIDEBAR_PREV_NEW       move the highlight to previous mailbox with new mail
	<sidebar-prev>           OP_SIDEBAR_PREV           move the highlight to previous mailbox
	<sidebar-toggle-virtual> OP_SIDEBAR_TOGGLE_VIRTUAL toggle between mailboxes and virtual mailboxes
	<sidebar-toggle-visible> OP_SIDEBAR_TOGGLE_VISIBLE make the sidebar (in)visible


Mailbox functions

Email functions

no pre-requisites
	<alias-dialog>                OP_ALIAS_DIALOG                     open the aliases dialog
	<autocrypt-acct-menu>         OP_AUTOCRYPT_ACCT_MENU              manage autocrypt accounts
	<change-folder-readonly>      OP_MAIN_CHANGE_FOLDER_READONLY      open a different folder in read only mode
	<change-folder>               OP_MAIN_CHANGE_FOLDER               open a different folder
	<change-newsgroup-readonly>   OP_MAIN_CHANGE_GROUP_READONLY       open a different newsgroup in read only mode
	<change-newsgroup>            OP_MAIN_CHANGE_GROUP                open a different newsgroup
	<change-vfolder>              OP_MAIN_CHANGE_VFOLDER              open a different virtual folder
	<create-alias>                OP_CREATE_ALIAS                     create an alias from a message sender
	<end-cond>                    OP_END_COND                         end of conditional execution (noop)
	<exit>                        OP_EXIT                             exit this menu
	<fetch-mail>                  OP_MAIN_FETCH_MAIL                  retrieve mail from POP server
	<forget-passphrase>           OP_FORGET_PASSPHRASE                wipe passphrases from memory
	<imap-fetch-mail>             OP_MAIN_IMAP_FETCH                  force retrieval of mail from IMAP server
	<imap-logout-all>             OP_MAIN_IMAP_LOGOUT_ALL             logout from all IMAP servers
	<mail-key>                    OP_MAIL_KEY                         mail a PGP public key
	<mail>                        OP_MAIL                             compose a new mail message
	<mailbox-list>                OP_MAILBOX_LIST                     list mailboxes with new mail
	<query>                       OP_QUERY                            query external program for addresses
	<quit>                        OP_QUIT                             save changes to mailbox and quit
	<recall-message>              OP_RECALL_MESSAGE                   recall a postponed message
	<sync-mailbox>                OP_MAIN_SYNC_FOLDER                 save changes to mailbox
	<vfolder-from-query-readonly> OP_MAIN_VFOLDER_FROM_QUERY_READONLY generate a read-only virtual folder from query
	<vfolder-from-query>          OP_MAIN_VFOLDER_FROM_QUERY          generate virtual folder from query

